  <body>
    <div style="text-align: center;"><h1>DHCP.io - Free Dynamic DNS</h1></div>

    <table width="100%">
      <tr><td width="15%" valign="top">
        </td>
        <td width="60%" valign="top">

          <h1>Welcome Home <!-- tmpl_var name='username' --></h1>
          <p>You're in charge of the hostname <b><tt><!-- tmpl_var name='username' escape='html' -->.dhcp.io</tt></b>.</p>
          <p>To update the value this points to please run:</p>
          <blockquote>
            <pre>
              $ curl http://dhcp.io/set/<!-- tmpl_var name='token' -->
            </pre>
          </blockquote>
          <p>If you wish to set the value to a specific IP please run:</p>
          <blockquote>
            <pre>
              $ curl http://dhcp.io/set/<!-- tmpl_var name='token' -->/1.2.3.4
            </pre>
          </blockquote>

          <p>Finally if you wish to avoid your URL being sniffed, stored, or copied, you could use a HTTP-POST instead:</p>
          <blockquote>
          <pre>
            $ curl -v -X POST curl http://dhcp.io/set --data 'token=<!-- tmpl_var name='token' -->&amp;ip=23.34.45.56'
          </pre>
          <p>(As before if you omit the <tt>ip=x.x.x.x</tt>  then the source of your request will be assumed.)</p>
          </blockquote>
        </td>
        <td width="25%" valign="top">
<!-- tmpl_include name='menu.inc' -->
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table>
